<item>
            <title>[LU-10291] remove concurrent_sends tunable</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10291</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Concurrent sends tunable was intended to limit the number of in-flight transfers per connection. However queue depth does the exact same job. So for example if the queue depth is negotiated to 16 and concurrent_sends is set to 32, the maximum number of in-flight transfers doesn&apos;t exceed 16. There is no need to keep concurrent_sends around since it doesn&apos;t add any unique functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
